## Style DNA (from Pinterest boards — 53 images analysed)
- "Quiet luxury with sneaker energy" — Southern European smart-casual
- Knit polo with button collar (long sleeve) is hero piece — grey, cream, mocha, navy
- Layering: knitwear over white shirt, blazer over crew-neck knit
- Colour palette: navy, black, stone/beige, cream/off-white, camel, grey, olive green
- Fit: slim through chest and shoulder, tapered leg — never baggy, never tight
- Brown leather everywhere: belt, shoes, bag always in cognac/tan
- Watch always on wrist
- Sneakers bridge both worlds: clean white leather for office-casual, heritage runners for leisure
- Zero loud logos. Subtle branding only.

## Shoe strategy (3 lanes)
1. Brown leather brogue / cap-toe oxford — for suits and smart days
2. Brown leather sneaker with white sole — smart-casual bridge
3. Heritage runner (NB 997/998/1500, Reebok Classic Nylon) — leisure

## Office style
Slim navy or charcoal blazer/suit + knit polo or sweater underneath + white sneakers or brown leather
Gingham shirt (navy or blue) + slim grey chinos + brown oxfords
No tie. Creative but polished.

## Casual style
Knit polo (open collar, short or long sleeve) + stone/beige slim chinos + white leather sneakers
Quarter-zip camel/beige knit + dark jeans + white tee underneath
Camel bomber + mid-wash jeans + white tee + white sneakers
Heritage runner as the statement piece with clean neutral outfit
